                                        Variable == "contact" ~ "contact communication type (categorical: 'cellular','telephone')", 
                                        Variable == "month" ~ "last contact month of year (categorical: 'jan', 'feb', 'mar', ..., 'nov', 'dec')",

2.2 Visualization

continous outcomes

# continous outcomes on average
subsidy %>%
  dplyr::select(y, age, previous, unemploy_rate, cons.price.idx, cons.conf.idx, inflation_rate, spent_on_repairs, inflation_rate, pdays) %>%
  gather(Variable, value, -y) %>%
  ggplot(aes(y, value, fill=y)) + 
    geom_bar(position = "dodge", stat = "summary", fun = "mean") + 
    facet_wrap(~Variable, scales = "free") +
    scale_fill_manual(values = palette2) +
    labs(x="Took the credit", y="Mean", 
         title = "Feature associations with the likelihood of taking the credit",
         subtitle = "(Continous outcomes on average)") +
    theme(legend.position = "none")

# continous outcomes in density
subsidy %>%
  dplyr::select(y, age, previous, unemploy_rate, cons.price.idx, cons.conf.idx, inflation_rate, spent_on_repairs, inflation_rate, pdays) %>%
    gather(Variable, value, -y) %>%
    ggplot() + 
    geom_density(aes(value, color=y), fill = "transparent") + 
    facet_wrap(~Variable, scales = "free") +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("#99CCCC","#FFCC99"),
                      name = 'Took Credit') +
    labs(title = "Feature associations with the likelihood of taking the credit",
         subtitle = "(continous outcomes in density)") +
    theme(legend.position = "none")

categorical outcomes

subsidy %>%
    dplyr::select(y,job, marital,education,contact, month, day_of_week, poutcome) %>%
    gather(Variable, value, -y) %>%
    count(Variable, value, y) %>%
      ggplot(., aes(value, n, fill = y)) +   
        geom_bar(position = "dodge", stat="identity") +
        facet_wrap(~Variable, scales="free") +
        scale_fill_manual(values = palette2) +
        labs(x="Click", y="Value",
             title = "Feature associations with the likelihood of taking the credit",
             subtitle = "Categorical features") +
        theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

Binary outcomes

subsidy %>%
    dplyr::select(y,mortgage, taxbill_in_phl, taxLien) %>%
    gather(Variable, value, -y) %>%
    count(Variable, value, y) %>%
      ggplot(., aes(value, n, fill = y)) +   
        geom_bar(position = "dodge", stat="identity") +
        facet_wrap(~Variable, ncol = 3, scales="free") +
        scale_fill_manual(values = palette2,
                          name = "Took Credit") +
        labs(x="Took Credit", y="Value",
             title = "Feature associations with the likelihood of taking credit",
             subtitle = "(Binary Features)")+
        theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

3.2 Feature engineering

# month
subsidy_eng <-
  subsidy %>%
  mutate(month = ifelse(month == "mar", "March", 
                                           "Other"))

# mariage
subsidy_eng <- 
  subsidy_eng %>%
  mutate(marital = case_when(marital == "divorced" ~ "notMarried",
                                  marital == "single" ~ "notMarried",
                                  marital == "unknown" ~ "unknown",
                                  marital == "married" ~ "married"
                                  ))

# Education
subsidy_eng <- 
  subsidy_eng %>%
  mutate(Education = 
           case_when(education == "basic.9y" |education == "basic.6y" | education == "basic.4y" ~ "Below High School",
                     education == "high.school"  ~ "High School",
                     education == "university.degree" |education == "professional.course"  ~ "Above Higher Education",
                     education == "unknown" ~ "unkown", education == "illiterate"  ~ "illiterate"))
    

# Job
subsidy_eng <-
  subsidy_eng %>%
  mutate(Job = case_when(
    job == "unknown" ~ "unknown", job == "retired" |job == "student" | job == "unemployed" ~ "Unemployed",
    job == "blue-collar" | job == "housemaid" | job == "self-employed" | job == "services"| job == "technician"  ~ "Average jobs",
    job == "admin." | job == "entrepreneur" | job == "management"  ~ "Higher position"))
set.seed(3456)
trainIndex2 <- createDataPartition(subsidy_eng$y, p = .65,
                                  list = FALSE,
                                  times = 1)
Training2 <- subsidy_eng[ trainIndex2,]
Test2  <- subsidy_eng[-trainIndex2,]
#
reg2 <- glm(y_numeric ~ .,
                  data=Training2 %>% dplyr::select(-campaign, -X, -y),
                  family="binomial" (link="logit"))

stargazer(reg1, reg2, type = "html", 
          title = "Table 3.4 Summary Statistics of Both Models on Training Set",
          header = FALSE,
